## EXPERIMENT – 03

## Virtual Lab

### Characterization and Parameter Extraction of the µA741 Operational Amplifier.

---

## Aim

The objective of this experiment is to determine the key parameters of the µA741 operational amplifier IC and compare the measured results with the standard specifications provided in its datasheet.

---

## Apparatus Required

The following components and instruments are required:

* µA741 IC
* Dual DC power supply
* Digital multimeter
* Function generator / A.F. oscillator
* CRO/DSO
* Breadboard
* Connecting wires

---

## Function Generator

A function generator is an electronic instrument used to produce different types of waveforms such as sine, square, and triangular signals. These signals are essential for testing and analyzing the behavior of electronic circuits.

