# Measurement of Non-Inverting Bias Current (IB₂)

The non-inverting bias current (IB₂) is the current entering the non-inverting input terminal of the op-amp.

## Procedure

1. Construct the circuit as shown for non-inverting bias current measurement.
2. Double-check all the connections.
3. Measure the output voltage using a digital multimeter.

## Formula

IB₂ = Vo / R₁

## Given Values

Vo = -0.020 V
R₁ = 470 kΩ = 470000 Ω

## Calculation

IB₂ = -0.020 / 470000
IB₂ = -4.255 × 10⁻⁸ A

Taking magnitude:

IB₂ ≈ 42.6 nA

